    "faq": {
      "type": "faq-accordion",
      "blocks": {
        "faq-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can a probiotic actually affect my hormone levels?",
            "answer": "<p>Origin doesn't add hormones to your body — it supports the gut bacteria that regulate how your body metabolizes and recycles the estrogen you already produce. The estrobolome (a community of gut bacteria identified by Plottel & Blaser, 2011) produces beta-glucuronidase, an enzyme that influences how much estrogen your body retains versus excretes. When estrobolome bacteria deplete, that regulatory system weakens. Origin supports the bacterial foundation that allows it to function more effectively.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long before I notice a difference?",
            "answer": "<p>Gut microbiome restoration is gradual. Most customers begin noticing changes in digestive comfort and energy within 2–3 weeks. Hormonal symptom changes — reduced hot flash frequency, more stable mood, improved sleep — typically become more apparent after 4–6 weeks of consistent use. We recommend at least 90 days for meaningful, sustained results. The 30-day guarantee covers you while you assess whether Origin is right for your biology.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I take Origin alongside HRT or bioidentical hormones?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Origin is a dietary supplement and does not interact with hormone replacement therapy or bioidentical hormone preparations. Many customers use Origin alongside existing hormone protocols — the goal is to support the gut ecosystem so your body can process hormones more effectively, whether those hormones are endogenous or supplemented. Always inform your healthcare provider about any new supplements you're taking.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Origin suitable during perimenopause and menopause?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Origin is designed for adults experiencing the hormonal shifts associated with perimenopause and menopause, as well as younger women dealing with cycle irregularities, PMS, or estrogen dominance symptoms. The estrobolome plays a role in estrogen metabolism across all stages of reproductive life. Because estrogen levels shift significantly during perimenopause, supporting the gut's capacity to regulate remaining estrogen becomes particularly important.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's in Origin and why those specific strains?",
            "answer": "<p>Origin contains 40 billion CFU across four strains: L. acidophilus (gut barrier, beta-glucuronidase support), B. lactis (immune function, gut integrity), L. plantarum (anti-inflammatory, broad cross-cultural fermented food strain), and L. paracasei (immune modulation, gut-brain axis). Each strain was selected based on environmental adaptation science and published clinical documentation. MAKTREK Bi-Pass marine polysaccharide delivery protects strains through stomach acid. FOS prebiotic feeds the bacteria on arrival. HPMC veggie capsule — no gelatin. Made in the USA in a cGMP-certified facility.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
